item.biomancy.mob_fang.tooltip: Cutting tooth made of Bone tissue rich in Bio-Minerals.
item.biomancy.mob_claw.tooltip: Hardened Claw made of tough fibers and rich in Bio-Minerals.
item.biomancy.mob_marrow.tooltip: Marrow extracted from the bones of your victims. Rich in Hormones and Bio-Minerals.
item.biomancy.withered_mob_marrow.toolti:
Withered Marrow, some dark fluid is oozing out of it.
Maybe you should suck it dry...
item.biomancy.mob_gland.tooltip: Organ sac filled with bile to the brim.
item.biomancy.toxin_gland.tooltip: A organ full of toxin, maybe you should drink this...
item.biomancy.volatile_gland.tooltip:
Gland filled with a reactive fluid.
Seems safe to drink...
item.biomancy.flesh_bits.tooltip: A tiny bit of flesh... Used as a primary crafting ingredient.
item.biomancy.bone_fragments.tooltip: A tiny fragment of bone... Provides rigidity and shape to flesh. Useful for assembling mechanical parts.
item.biomancy.tough_fibers.tooltip: Fibrous tissue that is very tough and rigid. Useful for crafting things that need more resilience.
item.biomancy.elastic_fibers.tooltip: Fibrous tissue that is sturdy but has rubbery properties. It appears like a good material to imitate muscles.
item.biomancy.mineral_fragment.tooltip:
Component only obtained in Decomposer.
Used to toughen and harden fibers.
item.biomancy.gem_fragments.tooltip: Used to enhance hardened fibers to their maximum resilience, very expensive.
item.biomancy.bio_lumens.tooltip:
Basic component, only obtained via the Decomposer, usually alongside biotic matter.

Used as a cosmetic upgrade to make things glow.
item.biomancy.organic_matter.tooltip: Moist organic material, extracted from Plants. With its dark and fibrous texture almost seems like humus.
item.biomancy.exotic_dust.tooltip: Exotic substance, maybe magical. Byproduct from decomposing magical things.
item.biomancy.stone_powder.tooltip: Very Basic Crafting component, usually obtained as a byproduct from decomposing things.
item.biomancy.nutrients.tooltip: Very hard pellets rich in energy, almost look like vitamin pills. Occasional byproduct from decomposing plants, but mainly obtained from digesting plants.
item.biomancy.nutrient_paste.tooltip: Nutrients combined with Biotic Matter to moisten the hard pellets and get a paste. Almost looks like yellowish cake, a useful source of energy.
item.biomancy.nutrient_bar.tooltip: Compressed Nutrient Paste into the shape of an edible Bar.
item.biomancy.regenerative_fluid.tooltip: Fluid that has regenerative properties, used to concoct healing additives.
item.biomancy.withering_ooze.tooltip: Corrosive extract, might have a bio-alchemical use.
item.biomancy.hormone_secretion.tooltip: A fluid extract very rich in hormones. Potent material for making drugs.
item.biomancy.volatile_fluid.tooltip: Combustible extract, needs further processing to be more dangerous.
item.biomancy.bile.tooltip: Organic base material which is often used in bio-alchemy.
item.biomancy.bone_cleaver.tooltip: A specialized bone tool for getting additional special loot from its victims.
item.biomancy.glass_vial.tooltip: Glass is transparent... very brittle, yet strong and rigid. Very high alchemical resistance, seems perfect for holding reactive substances.
item.biomancy.living_flesh.tooltip:
It's alive!
But it looks too dumb to be the brain of a mob. You should turn it into a construct.
item.biomancy.primordial_living_flesh.to: A ominous piece of primal flesh oozing primordial soup. It looks hungry...
item.biomancy.primordial_living_oculus.t: A ominous eye is gazing at you...
item.biomancy.creator_mix.tooltip: A meal made for the cradle... just not for you.
item.biomancy.injector.tooltip: A simple device which utilizes a razor sharp needle to quickly and forcefully inject Serums into Mobs and Players.
item.biomancy.fertilizer.tooltip: Fertilizer that induces hyper-growth in plants, even for reeds, cactus, nether wart and chorus plant.
item.biomancy.long_claws.tooltip:
Claws made of living flesh

Feed it with nutrients via right click in the inventory.
item.biomancy.bile_spitter.tooltip:
WIP: "living" projectile weapon that shoots corrosive bile.
Intended behaviour: charge it like a bow to increase damage & size of projectile.
item.biomancy.organic_compound.tooltip: Slimy substance made of bile infused with nutrients.
item.biomancy.unstable_compound.tooltip: Very unstable and reactive substance. Seems like it will combust if it comes in contact with other things.
item.biomancy.exotic_compound.tooltip: Substance of a questionable nature, comprised of exotic material and other trace elements.
item.biomancy.genetic_compound.tooltip: Cocktail of various hormones, nutrients and organic elements. Compound that seems useful for producing potent stimulants.
item.biomancy.corrosive_additive.tooltip: An highly corrosive fluid that seems useful for alchemically burning away organic material or weakening the bonds of complex substances.
item.biomancy.healing_additive.tooltip: An highly concentrated substance that is used to imbue it properties to other compounds.
serum.biomancy.ageing_serum.tooltip: Forces the maturation of young Mobs into Adults. Some rare Mobs may turn into Elders.
serum.biomancy.rejuvenation_serum.toolti: Reverses the maturation of Mobs, in most cases they turn into children.
serum.biomancy.enlargement_serum.tooltip:
Induces growth in Slimes, Magma Cubes and Flesh Blobs.

(If Pehkui is installed you can enlarge yourself and all Mobs)
serum.biomancy.shrinking_serum.tooltip:
Shrinks Slimes, Magma Cubes and Flesh Blobs.

(If Pehkui is installed you can shrink yourself and all Mobs)
serum.biomancy.cleansing_serum.tooltip:
Burns away all foreign substances inside a living entity.
Very effective for sticky status effects that refuse to be healed with milk.
serum.biomancy.breeding_stimulant.toolti: Makes Animals hyper-fertile, making them able to constantly reproduce for a short time.
serum.biomancy.absorption_boost.tooltip: Grants stackable absorption health points for Mobs and Players.
serum.biomancy.insomnia_cure.tooltip: Resets the last slept time, no need to sleep for quite some time.
block.biomancy.primordial_cradle.tooltip: Offer adequate Tributes to the cradle and summon forth primordial messengers of exquisite flesh.
block.biomancy.decomposer.tooltip:
A bio-machine that deconstructs items into their base components.
The bio-machine consumes nutrients to function.
block.biomancy.digester.tooltip: A machine born from flesh that converts food and plants into nutrients.
block.biomancy.tongue.tooltip: Extracts up to 3 items of the same type every 24 ticks from containers its attached to and drops them on the ground.
block.biomancy.maw_hopper.tooltip: A fleshy sister of the hopper. Transfers up to 16 items at a time.
block.biomancy.storage_sac.tooltip: Cheap Shulker-like storage sac that also works like a bundle.
block.biomancy.fleshkin_chest.tooltip:
A fleshkin forged into the shape of a chest with sharp teeth and a resilient stomach allowing it to keeps its contents when mined.
Only its master may open and takes its content without repercussion.

It's fangs look awfully sharp...
block.biomancy.fleshkin_pressure_plate.t:
Fleshkin pancake. Yummy...
It has two behaviors, either it only activates for its owner or it only works for everyone else.

Sneak click to change its behavior.
block.biomancy.flesh.tooltip: A generic block of flesh... Don't bother me with this!
block.biomancy.flesh_slab.tooltip: A generic slab of flesh... Don't bother me with this!
block.biomancy.flesh_stairs.tooltip: Stairs made of generic flesh... Don't bother me with this!
block.biomancy.packed_flesh.tooltip: Tenacious Block of flesh. Is it tough enough?
block.biomancy.packed_flesh_slab.tooltip: Tenacious Slab of flesh. Is it tough enough?
block.biomancy.packed_flesh_stairs.toolt: Stairs made of tenacious flesh. Is it tough enough?
block.biomancy.flesh_fence.tooltip: Fence made of bones and flesh...
block.biomancy.flesh_fence_gate.tooltip: Fence gate made of bones and flesh...
block.biomancy.flesh_iris_door.tooltip: Trapdoor-like iris door made of flesh...
block.biomancy.flesh_door.tooltip: A sliding door made of flesh...
block.biomancy.full_flesh_door.tooltip: A wide sliding door made of flesh...
block.biomancy.bone_spike.tooltip: A dangerous spike made of reinforced bone, colliding with it will hurt.
block.biomancy.flesh_ladder.tooltip: Ladder mainly made of bones and a little bit of flesh...
block.biomancy.primal_flesh.tooltip: Primitive and pure, you better not touch this with your dirty paws.
block.biomancy.primal_flesh_slab.tooltip: Primitive and pure, you better not touch this with your dirty paws.
block.biomancy.primal_flesh_stairs.toolt: Stairs made of primal flesh. Feels primitive and pure...
block.biomancy.corrupted_primal_flesh.to: It's no longer pure... Don't deny it. Your dirty paws caused this!
block.biomancy.malignant_flesh.tooltip: Looks dangerous, you better not touch this block!
block.biomancy.malignant_flesh_slab.tool: Looks dangerous, you better not touch this slab!
block.biomancy.malignant_flesh_stairs.to: Stairs made of malignant flesh. Looks diseased...
block.biomancy.malignant_flesh_veins.too: Looks dangerous, you better not touch these veins!
death.attack.biomancy.chest_bite: %1$s tried touching a chest but was eaten instead
death.attack.biomancy.creator_spikes: %1$s angered the Maykrs and was impaled by bone spikes
death.attack.biomancy.bone_spike_impale: %1$s was impaled by a sharp bone
death.attack.biomancy.tooth_projectile: %1$s was forcefully implanted with teeth by %2$s
death.attack.biomancy.tooth_projectile.i: %1$s received a lethal dental implant by %2$s using %3$s
death.attack.biomancy.corrosive_acid_pro: %1$s was doused with corrosive acid by %2$s
%1$s was showered in corrosive acid by %2$s using %3$s
jer.biomancy.requiresDespoilOrBoneCleave: Requires Despoil Enchantment or Bone Cleaver (#forge:tools/knives)
advancements.biomancy.root.title: Meat Whisperer
advancements.biomancy.root.description: You feel a presence in the flesh, it whispers into your ears: "Raw Meat is useful..."
advancements.biomancy.greedy_butcher.des: You've acquired a taste for organs. Crafted a special tool to get them fresh from your victims death.
advancements.biomancy.organ_trader.title: Organ Trader
advancements.biomancy.organ_trader.descr: Become the funnel for fleshy parts and trade various organs with villagers.
advancements.biomancy.poacher.title: Rare Animal Poacher
advancements.biomancy.poacher.descriptio: You have no morals and poached endangered Animals.
advancements.biomancy.predator_killer.de: Hunt predators and collect their fangs and claws.
advancements.biomancy.cat_killer.title: Kitty Cat Killer
advancements.biomancy.flesh.title: Strange Vision
advancements.biomancy.flesh.description: You felt a foreign presence from the ender eye. A cauldron made of raw meat appears in your mind, you start forgetting portals... you feel compelled to build it...
advancements.biomancy.living_flesh.title: Reviving Flesh
advancements.biomancy.living_flesh.descr: You felt a foreign presence from the ender eye. A cauldron made of raw meat appears in your mind, you start forgetting portals... you feel compelled to build it...
advancements.biomancy.healing_activator_: It's seems like fluids enriched in life energy are needed. Jumpstart the process with a few healing potions.
advancements.biomancy.raw_meat_sacrifice: Serve raw meat to the Primordial Cradle.
advancements.biomancy.cooked_meat_sacrif: Serve cooked meat to the Primordial Cradle.
advancements.biomancy.decomposer.title: Munch & Crunch
advancements.biomancy.decomposer.descrip: You suddenly feel disgusted by the composter. You should use a semi-living construct to decompose things into their base parts.
advancements.biomancy.bio_forge.title: Organic Smithing
advancements.biomancy.bio_forge.descript: You dreamt of a Bio-Construct weaving organic parts together into intricate semi-living things... You don't know when, but you built it.
advancements.biomancy.digester.title: Yummy Paste
advancements.biomancy.digester.descripti: You feel tired of feeding your Bio-Constructs with poor quality food. You have the urge to produce a nutrients enriched yellow-green paste.
advancements.biomancy.bio_lab.title: Is this still Alchemy?
advancements.biomancy.bio_lab.descriptio: You had an epiphany, why use crude inorganic tools to brew potions if an Bio-Construct can do it better. No longer do you need to mix or adjust the heat by yourself.
advancements.biomancy.bio_injector.title: Injections
advancements.biomancy.bio_injector.descr: Craft a Bio-Injector to be able to forcefully inject Serums into all living things.
Combine various organic secretions and substances to create Compounds and Serums.
advancements.biomancy.exotic_compounds.d: Combine organic things with exotic compounds to create cures and cleansing fluids.
Combine organic things with genetic compounds to create fluids that influence growth and fertility.
book.biomancy.guide_book.features.multib: Multi-block pages allow to preview multi-blocks both in the book and in the world.
book.biomancy.guide_book.features.recipe: Recipe pages allow to show recipes in the book.
A smelting recipe page with one recipe and some text.
book.biomancy.guide_book.features.spotli: Spotlight pages allow to show items (actually, ingredients).
A sample spotlight page with custom title.
A sample spotlight page with automatic title.
book.biomancy.guide_book.features.entity: Entity pages allow to show entities.
A sample entity page with automatic title.
book.biomancy.guide_book.features.name: Features Category
book.biomancy.guide_book.name: Biomancy Index
book.biomancy.guide_book.tooltip: A book to test Modonomicon features for Biomancy.
